KINGDOMS of ENGLAND

Text by Mad Mel


     This is a game, that is quite a bit like Defenders of the Crown (cinemaware.)  Your goal is to conquer the island country of what is now England.  At the beginning of the game, you can select what percentage of the land must be owned before a winner is proclaimed, however, the smaller the %, the faster the game and the computer players are very quick at these levels.

     To start the game, you will be shown 4 flags and these flags are the possible Human Players.  Click on a flag and then enter the name for the kingdom.  If you are only playing one human, then now click on the done icon.  This first screen also holds the percentage option.  Up to 4 humans can play against each other and 4 computer players.  No matter what, there are always 4 computer players in the game.

     Now your quest begins and you must move out smartly.  Here in the very beginning of the game, is where you will ultimately win or lose the game.  Build all three of your armies and leave some in your castle army.  This will give you 4 armies you can move out on your first move.  Take 4 sections of land right at the start (if 4 are available to you.)  Then continue on and good luck.

Game Options:

To find out the Silver value of a piece of land, or to see the other stats, simply click on the section.

To enter the option screen for any section of land you own, press the left button to select the land, then the right button to enter the options.  You may need to try this a couple times, as the option is a little touchy.  If you have a problem, press and hold the left and when you see your stats, press the right and the options should appear.

STATS SCREEN:
NAME: name of land                     OWNER: name of player
SILVER: amount of silver per turn
TERRAIN: type of ground
MOVEMENT USAGE: number of movement turns it takes to enter the land.

If this is your land, your armies occupying the section will be shown in the right hand section.

