 EXPLANATION of ITEMS FOUND ABOVE:

Hiring Men.  You will be asked which army to hire for and you can pick.  I find it easier to hire for the castle army and then just split up the armies.  This way, you see the total amount of each type of man and you can more evenly disperse them.  When you select the army to build, you will be shown a list of the men available and the cost.  The more expensive, the better fighter he is.  To hire a man, click on the numbers to the right of the men you want.  Left button selects one at a time and hold left press right to select ten at a time.

Splitting Armies.  This is the way to take men from one army and place them in another.  You will be asked to pick the originating army and then to pick the receiving army.  If you don't have any armies to receive, just click in the space directly below your 1st army and your next army will be formed.  You can have 1 castle army and 3 movement armies.

Moving Castle or Movement Armies.  These move exactly the same way.  Click the Move Army or MV Castle option for the army you want to move and then click the section of land you wish to move into.  Make sure your army has enough movement points (listed with the army) to enter the land.  When moving, if you have 5 mv points and the land your entering needs 3, you can't move through to the next section of land, unless you own the 1st already.  In other words, you can't move through a section of free land or a section owned by another player.

Building.  This is easy to understand.  If you have an expensive piece of land or a critical border, you may want to put up a castle.  You can do this in sections, improving with each move.  This increases the defensive % of your section of land.

Silver.  This is how much each section of land makes per move.  You can then use this money (which is all pooled together) to hire men and buy catapults.

When you finish a turn, click the left, then the right on the DONE icon.
        
